claim.claim-text:
1. A method for reserving a service initially reserved to another user comprising the steps of: 
creating a backup queue containing users interested in the initially reserved service; 
detecting a cancellation of the reserved service; 
determining the availability of users in the backup queue for the cancelled service; 
notifying an available user from the backup queue that the service is available for use; and 
reserving the cancelled service for the notified user from the backup queue.

12. The method as described in claim 11 wherein the user does not accept the reservation and further comprising: 
determining the next available user in the queue; 
notifying the available user of the available reservation; 
determining whether notified user has accepted the reservation; and 
repeating said steps herein until a notified user accepts the reservation.

16. The method as described in claim 3 wherein said user availability step further comprises: 
creating a reservation status profile; 
comparing the reservation status profile with the notification profile for each user in the queue; 
determining whether there is match between the reservation status profile and the user notification profiles in the queue; and 
selecting the user with the profile that is the closest match to the reservation status profile.

18. A method for reserving a resource, which automatically re-books the resource in the event of the cancellation of the existing reservation of the resource comprising the steps of: 
reserving a resource for a user; 
receiving reservations for the previously reserved resource 
when a reservation is received for the previously reserved resource, creating a backup queue containing users interested in reserving the previously reserved resource; 
detecting a cancellation of the reserved resource; 
determining the availability of users in the backup queue for the cancelled resource; 
notifying an available user from the backup queue that the resource is available for use; and 
reserving the cancelled resource for the notified user from the backup queue.

24. The method as described in claim 23 wherein the user does not accept the reservation and further comprising: 
determining the next available user in the queue; 
notifying the available user of the available reservation; 
determining whether notified user has accepted the reservation; and 
repeating said steps herein until a notified user accepts the reservation.

25. The method as described in claim 20 wherein said user availability step further comprises: 
creating a reservation status profile; 
comparing the reservation status profile with the notification profile for each user in the queue; 
determining whether there is match between the reservation status profile and the user notification profiles in the queue; and 
selecting the user with the profile that is the closest match to the reservation status profile.

30. A computer program product in a computer readable medium method for reserving a resource, which automatically re-books the resource in the event of the cancellation of the existing reservation of the resource comprising: 
instructions for reserving a resource for a user; 
instructions for receiving reservations for the previously reserved resource 
when a reservation is received for the previously reserved resource, instructions for creating a backup queue containing users interested in reserving the previously reserved resource; 
instructions for detecting a cancellation of the reserved resource; 
instructions for determining the availability of users in the backup queue for the cancelled resource; 
instructions for notifying an available user from the backup queue that the resource is available for use; and 
instructions for reserving the cancelled resource for the notified user from the backup queue.

36. The computer program product as described in claim 35 wherein the user does not accept the reservation and further comprising: 
instructions for determining the next available user in the queue; 
instructions for notifying the available user of the available reservation; 
instructions for determining whether notified user has accepted the reservation; and 
instructions for repeating said steps herein until a notified user accepts the reservation.

37. The computer program product as described in claim 32 wherein said user availability instructions further comprise: 
instructions for creating a reservation status profile; 
instructions for comparing the reservation status profile with the notification profile for each user in the queue; 
instructions for determining whether there is match between the reservation status profile and the user notification profiles in the queue; and 
instructions for selecting the user with the profile that is the closest match to the reservation status profile.

38. A system for reserving a resource, which automatically re-books the resource in the event of the cancellation of the existing reservation for the resource, said system comprising: 
a backup queue containing the names of users interested in reserving a previously reserved resource; 
a device for detecting the cancellation of a reservation for a resource; 
a decision-making element that determines the availability of users in said backup queue for the now available resource; 
a notification element that notifies an interested user, determined from said backup queue, that the resource is available; and 
a reservation center, where the rebooking of the available resource to a notified user from the backup queue occurs.

40. The system as described in claim 38 further comprising; 
a device for remote use by a user interested in reserving the available resource, said device enabling communication between the user and the reservation center; and 
a communication medium through which said reservation center and said device communicate with each other.
